<div class="topic-card"><strong>Part 2: Submitting Your Project in the LMS</strong></div>

<section class="chapter-section">
<div class="chapter-text">
<p><span style="font-size:18px;">Now, submit your awesome work! You&rsquo;ll create a simple document (like in Google Docs or Microsoft Word) and upload it to your LMS.</span></p>

<h2><strong>Step 1: Create the Submission Document</strong></h2>

<ul>
	<li>Open a new document in Google Docs, Word, or any word processor.</li>
	<li>At the top, write:</li>
	<li><strong>Name:</strong> [Your Full Name]</li>
	<li><strong>Grade:</strong> [Your Grade, e.g., 5th Grade]</li>
	<li><strong>Date:</strong> October 10, 2025</li>
	<li>Then, add:</li>
	<li><strong>Website Link:</strong> Paste the Gamma URL here (e.g., https://gamma.app/your-project-link).</li>
	<li><strong>Key Features:</strong> List 3-5 cool things about your page, like:</li>
	<li>&quot;Fun welcome section with a big jewellery photo!&quot;</li>
	<li>&quot;List of materials like brass and enamel with pictures.&quot;</li>
	<li>&quot;AI-generated images of sparkly designs.&quot;</li>
	<li>&quot;Easy-to-read info on anti-tarnish technology.&quot;</li>
	<li>&quot;Colorful theme inspired by the sea.&quot;</li>
	<li>Keep it short and fun&mdash;1 page is enough!</li>
</ul>

<h2><strong>Step 2: Save and Export the Document</strong></h2>

<ul>
	<li>Save the file as &quot;[Your Name] - Salty Jewellery Project.docx&quot; or &quot;.pdf&quot;.</li>
	<li>If your LMS needs a PDF, export it as one (in Google Docs, go to File &gt; Download &gt; PDF).</li>
</ul>

<h2><strong>Step 3: Upload to LMS</strong></h2>

<ul>
	<li>Log in to your school&rsquo;s LMS (ask your teacher if you&rsquo;re not sure how).</li>
	<li>Go to the assignment for &quot;Capstone Project&quot; and click &quot;Submit&quot; or &quot;Turn In&quot;.</li>
	<li>Upload your document file.</li>
	<li>If there&rsquo;s a text box, paste your website link there too, just in case.</li>
	<li>Hit submit&mdash;done! Your teacher will love it.</li>
</ul>

<p><span style="font-size:18px;">Great job, young designer! This project shows off what you&rsquo;ve learned about Salty Jewellery&rsquo;s cool materials and innovations. If you have questions, ask your teacher. Have fun creating! ✨</span></p>
